@Node "Overview" "MakeMPIndex.guide/Overview"
@Next "Parameters"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Quick overview
**************

@{b}MPIndex@{ub} is a tool for indexing AmigaGuide documents - similar to the
Windows Help Search facility.

@{b}MakeMPIndex@{ub} is used to generate the index.

@{b}RunMPIndex@{ub} can then be used to display a Gui which allows the index to
be view and specific nodes selected.

An example usage is to index all of your .guide files.

To do this do:

     @{b}list sys: work: pat=#?.guide all to=t:i1 lformat=%s%s@{ub}
       Where "sys: work:" are the drives on your system.
     
     Then edit t:i1 if required to remove any files
     which you do not need to index and/or reorder
     the list of files.
     
     @{b}MakeMPIndex t:i2 maxnode=20 file=t:i1 ignoreto=t:i3@{ub}
     
     Then edit t:i3 to remove any words which you do
     not want to ignore.
     
     @{b}MakeMPIndex docs.index file=t:i1 ignore=t:i3@{ub}
     
     Then @{b}RunMPIndex@{ub} can be used to view the index.


@EndNode

@Node "Parameters" "MakeMPIndex.guide/Parameters"
@Next "Algorithms"
@Prev "Overview"
@Toc "Main"

Shell parameters
****************

The following parameters can be supplied:


 @{" TO/A        " Link "TO"}         Destination Index file
 @{" MERGE/K     " Link "MERGE"}         Index file to merge
 @{" IGNORE/K    " Link "IGNORE"}         List of words to ignore
 @{" IGNORETO/K  " Link "IGNORETO"}         Saved file of ignore words
 @{" MAXNODE/K/N " Link "MAXNODE"}         Maximum number of references
 @{" NODE/S      " Link "NODE"}         Use node name for title?
 @{" NODE2/S     " Link "NODE2"}         Use 2nd node name for title?
 @{" TITLE/S     " Link "TITLE"}         Use title for title?
 @{" FILE/K      " Link "FILE"}         List of files to index
 @{" FROM/M      " Link "FROM"}         List of .guide files to index

e.g. The command to make the index for MPIndex could be:

     MakeMPIndex Docs.Index Ignore=IgnoreWord MaxNode=10 RunMPIndex.guide MakeMPIndex.guide


@EndNode

@Node "TO" "MakeMPIndex.guide/TO"
@Next "MERGE"
@Toc "Parameters"

TO Parameter
============

This gives the name of the Index file to generate.

Use Docs.Index to create the default file for @{b}RunMPIndex@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "MERGE" "MakeMPIndex.guide/MERGE"
@Next "IGNORE"
@Prev "TO"
@Toc "Parameters"

MERGE Parameter
===============

This gives the name of an Index file (previously generated by
@{b}MakeMPIndex@{ub}) to merge.

This allows an index to be generated with @{"NODE" Link "NODE"} set on some .guides and
not on others.


@EndNode

@Node "IGNORE" "MakeMPIndex.guide/IGNORE"
@Next "IGNORETO"
@Prev "MERGE"
@Toc "Parameters"

IGNORE Parameter
================

This gives the name of a file (with a single word per line) which lists
words which should not be indexed.

This allows common words (e.g. @{b}and@{ub}) to not be included in the index.

See also @{"MAXNODE" Link "MAXNODE"}.


@EndNode

@Node "IGNORETO" "MakeMPIndex.guide/IGNORETO"
@Next "MAXNODE"
@Prev "IGNORE"
@Toc "Parameters"

IGNORETO Parameter
==================

This gives the name of a file which will hold a list of all the words
which have been ignored.

See also @{"IGNORE" Link "IGNORE"}.


@EndNode

@Node "MAXNODE" "MakeMPIndex.guide/MAXNODE"
@Next "NODE"
@Prev "IGNORETO"
@Toc "Parameters"

MAXNODE Parameter
=================

This gives the maximum number of nodes a word can appear in before it
is not included in the index.

This allows common words to not be included in the index.

If not supplied then there is no limit.

Also see @{"IGNORE" Link "IGNORE"}.


@EndNode

@Node "NODE" "MakeMPIndex.guide/NODE"
@Next "NODE2"
@Prev "MAXNODE"
@Toc "Parameters"

NODE Parameter
==============

This specifies that the first format of the node name should be used as
the title.

See @{"Algorithms" Link "Algorithms"}.


@EndNode

@Node "NODE2" "MakeMPIndex.guide/NODE2"
@Next "TITLE"
@Prev "NODE"
@Toc "Parameters"

NODE2 Parameter
===============

This specifies that the second format of the node name should be used
as the title.

See @{"Algorithms" Link "Algorithms"}.


@EndNode

@Node "TITLE" "MakeMPIndex.guide/TITLE"
@Next "FILE"
@Prev "NODE2"
@Toc "Parameters"

TITLE Parameter
===============

This specifies that the title of the node should be used as the title.

See @{"Algorithms" Link "Algorithms"}.


@EndNode

@Node "FILE" "MakeMPIndex.guide/FILE"
@Next "FROM"
@Prev "TITLE"
@Toc "Parameters"

FILE Parameter
==============

This specifies a file which holds a list of files to index.

Also see @{"FROM" Link "FROM"}.


@EndNode

@Node "FROM" "MakeMPIndex.guide/FROM"
@Prev "FILE"
@Toc "Parameters"

FROM Parameter
==============

This specifies a list of .guide files to index.

Also see @{"FILE" Link "FILE"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Algorithms" "MakeMPIndex.guide/Algorithms"
@Next "Bugs"
@Prev "Parameters"
@Toc "Main"

Alogorithms for the title
*************************

There are various ways in which the title of an AmigaGuide node can be
held in the file.

e.g. If a Node starts with the following...

     @Node "Overview" "RunMPIndex.guide/Overview"
     @Next "Installation"
     @Prev "Main"
     @Toc "Main"
     @title RunMPIndex Quick Overview
     
     Quick overview
     **************

Then the following could be considered the title:

     1 Overview
     2 RunMPIndex.guide/Overview
     3 RunMPIndex Quick Overview
     4 Quick overview

Any @title @{b}4@{ub} will be used if present.

If @{"TITLE" Link "TITLE"} is supplied then @{b}3@{ub} will be used.

If @{"NODE2" Link "NODE2"} is supplied then @{b}2@{ub} will be used.

If @{"NODE" Link "NODE"} is supplied then @{b}1@{ub} will be used.

However, if a duplicate title is produced in one file then there is a
fallback from 4, to 3, to 2, to 1.

If none of @{"TITLE" Link "TITLE"}, @{"NODE2" Link "NODE2"} and @{"NODE" Link "NODE"} are supplied then the mechanism of
determining the title is guessed:

If @{b}makeinfo@{ub} is found in the file before the first node then @{"TITLE" Link "TITLE"} is
assumed.

If the second node names of the second and third nodes are the same
then @{"NODE" Link "NODE"} is assumed.

If any of the second node names of the fourth to the twentieth nodes
include spaces then @{"NODE2" Link "NODE2"} is assumed.

If all of this fails then @{"NODE" Link "NODE"} is assumed.

This should hopefully produce valid titles on all guide files. If it
does not then you can always override the guessing. Also please let me
@{"know" Link "Distribution"} of the file.


@EndNode

@Node "Bugs" "MakeMPIndex.guide/Bugs"
@Next "History"
@Prev "Algorithms"
@Toc "Main"

Known (and unknown) errors
**************************

@{b}MakeMPIndex@{ub} has horrible stack usage and a large stack is highly
recommended for efficiency.

These docs are a bit sparse.


@EndNode

@Node "History" "MakeMPIndex.guide/History"
@Next "Distribution"
@Prev "Bugs"
@Toc "Main"

Version History
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} Version 5.5

        @{b}*@{ub} Opens locale.library(38) to work on OS3.0.

   @{b}*@{ub} Version 5.4

        @{b}*@{ub} Allow spaces in node names.

        @{b}*@{ub} Bug fix for nodes with all words ignored.

        @{b}*@{ub} Remove spaces at the start of a title.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added IGNORETO parameter.

        @{b}*@{ub} Memory saving when ignoring words.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added CTRL-C checking.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added TITLE parameter.

        @{b}*@{ub} Can now guess how to determine the title.

        @{b}*@{ub} No longer produces duplicate titles.

        @{b}*@{ub} Uses @title.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added details of stack usage.

        @{b}*@{ub} Prints file names, node titles and ignored words.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added FILE parameter.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added docs on how to index lots of files.

   @{b}*@{ub} Version beta1 5.3

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed MERGE - was completely broken in 5.2!

        @{b}*@{ub} Recompiled using SAS/C 6.57.

        @{b}*@{ub} Localised.

   @{b}*@{ub} Version 5.2

        @{b}*@{ub} Uses lower case version of words if present. Thanks to Tom
          Byrer.

        @{b}*@{ub} IGNORE now works. Thanks to Tom Byrer.

        @{b}*@{ub} Changed the file format - reduced memory usage.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added IgnoreWord and example usage for MakeMPIndex.

   @{b}*@{ub} Version 5.1

        @{b}*@{ub} Some memory improvements

        @{b}*@{ub} NODE2 parameter

   @{b}*@{ub} Version 5.0

        @{b}*@{ub} First Version released


@EndNode

